Package calculator

Class Stack

java.lang.Object
calculator.Stack
public class Stack extends Object
Class for handling the Stack of Entry values. Allows a new Stack to be created and the Entries on it to be manipulated.
Author:
Hayden Amarr

    • push

      public void push(Entry entry)
      Adds an new entry to the stack and increments the value containing the size of the list (Stack).

    • top

      public Entry top()
      Returns the entry at the top of the Stack and does not remove it. If the Stack is empty then return an EmptyStackException.
      Returns:
      The entry at the top of the Stack

    • size

      public int size()
      Getter for the size field. This is the number of Entries stored in the Stack.
      Returns:
      size The number of items in the Stack.

    • pop

      public Entry pop()
      Remove and return the Entry at the top of the Stack. But throw an EmptyStackException if the Stack is Empty.
      Returns:
      Entry Record at the top of the Stack
